\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Connectors are automatically formatted.  This is particularly useful  in situations where their endpoints are broken across a system, as shown in an example below.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Tie connecting chords are automatically formatted so as to avoid colliding with dots, accidentals, and wrong-side noteheads.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa80\li0\ri0\f1\fs32\b1\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\b To make a connector\b0  \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Make a selection of staff objects.  Click the Connector Tool (shown above).  The connector will appear in its default placement. The connector will be selected.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 The connector wll be placed relative to the notes in the selection.  Ties and Slurs have different connection rules, and require two connectable objects in the selection. The placement of other connectors such as hairpins and voltas depends on the disposition of the objects within the selection.  The Connector Tool is one-shot.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 If the two selected endpoints are chords, then ties will be created and formatted according to standard conventions.  Otherwise, a slur will be created.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa80\li0\ri0\f1\fs32\b1\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\b To alter the connector placement\b0  \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 The default placement is correct for most situations.  However, either endpoint of a connector may be dragged to a new location relative to the note to which it is attached.  Also, when a staff object is moved, any connectors attached to the staff object are automatically repositioned into the appropriate placement.  If the connector placement is \fs24\f1\b0\i0 f\f1 ree\f0  (see below), the default placement for the given situation is used.  If the connector placement is  \fs24\f1\b0\i0 f\f1 ixed\f0 , the specified placement (see below) is used.  The default is \fs24\f1\b0\i0 f\f1 ree\f0  mode. However, after a manual adjustment is made to an endpoint, Calliope will automatically assume that the connector is henceforth in \fs24\f1\b0\i0 f\f1 ixed\f0  mode unless changed back using the inspector.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Connectors also automatically format to accommodate the change in layout resulting from system adjustments or spilling and grabbing of bars.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 The shape of ties and slurs may be changed by dragging any of the four control points of the connector. \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa80\li0\ri0\f1\fs32\b1\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Inspecting Connectors\par
